quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,Is he not aware of the time when the contents of the graves will be brought out
  100,10,And the hearts' contents shall be brought into the open
  100,11,"Surely, on that Day, they will know that their Lord had full knowledge of them all"
  101,1,The Clatterer
  101,2,What is the Clatterer
  101,3,Would that you knew what the Clatterer is
  101,4,"[It is] a Day when mankind shall be like scattered moths"
  101,5,and the mount-ains like tufts of carded wool
  101,6,"Then, the one whose good deeds weigh heavy on the scales"
  101,7,will have a most pleasing life
  101,8,But as for him whose deeds are light on the scales
  101,9,the Abyss shall be his home
  101,10,What will convey to you what this is like
  101,11,It is a blazing fire
  102,1,"Greed for more and more distracted you [from God]"
  102,2,till you reached the grave
  102,3,But you will soon come to know
  102,4,But you will soon come to know
  102,5,"Indeed, were you to know the truth with certainty"
  102,6,you would see the fire of Hell
  102,7,You would see it with the eye of certainty
  102,8,Then on that Day you shall be questioned about your worldly favours
  103,1,I swear by the passage of time
  103,2,that man is surely in a state of loss
  103,3,"except for those who believe and do good deeds and exhort one another to hold fast to the Truth, and who exhort one another to stead-fastness"
  104,1,Woe to every fault-finding back-biter
  104,2,"who amasses wealth, counting it over"
  104,3,thinking that his wealth will make him live forever
  104,4,By no means! He shall surely be cast into the crushing torment
  104,5,Would that you understood what that crushing torment is like
  104,6,It is a Fire kindled by God
  104,7,Reaching right into the hearts of men
  104,8,it closes in on them from every side
  104,9,in towering columns
  105,1,Have you not seen how your Lord dealt with the people of the elephant
  105,2,Did He not foil their strategy
  105,3,and send against them flocks of birds
  105,4,which pelted them with clay stones
  105,5,Thus He made them like stubble cropped by cattle
  106,1,For the security of the Quraysh
  106,2,their security in their winter and summer journeys
  106,3,So let them worship the Lord of this House
  106,4,who provided them with food lest they go hungry and saved them from fear
  107,1,Have you seen one who denies the Day of Judgement
  107,2,Who turns away the orphan
  107,3,and who does not urge the feeding of the poor
  107,4,So woe to those who pray
  107,5,but whose hearts are not in their prayer
  107,6,Those who do things only to be seen by others
  107,7,Who are uncharitable even over very small things
  108,1,We have given you abundance
  108,2,Pray to your Lord and sacrifice to Him alone
  108,3,It is the one who hates you who has been cut off
  109,1,"Say, \"You who deny the Truth"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,You do not worship what I worship
  109,4,I will never worship what you worship
  109,5,You will never worship what I worship
  109,6,You have your religion and I have mine
  110,1,When God's help and victory come
  110,2,and you see people entering God's religion in multitudes
  110,3,then glorify your Lord with His praise and seek His forgiveness. He is always ready to accept repentance
  111,1,"May the hands of Abu Lahab perish, may he be ruined"
  111,2,Neither his wealth nor his gains will avail him
  111,3,He shall soon enter a Blazing Fire
  111,4,and also his wife who carries the fuel
  111,5,with a rope of twisted fibre round her neck
  112,1,"Say, \"He is God, the One"
  112,2,"God, the Self-sufficient One"
  112,3,"He does not give birth, nor was He born"
  112,4,and there is nothing like Him
  113,1,"Say, \"I seek refuge in the Lord of the daybreak"
  113,2,from the evil of what He has created
  113,3,from the evil of darkness as it descends
  113,4,from the evil of those who blow on knots
  113,5,and from the evil of the envier when he envies
  114,1,"Say, \"I seek refuge in the Lord of people"
  114,2,the King of people
  114,3,the God of people
  114,4,from the mischief of every sneaking whis-perer
  114,5,who whispers into the hearts of people
  114,6,from jinn and men